            "value": "Here are some of the most useful Windows 11 shortcuts people often forget:\n\nWin + V \u2014 Clipboard history (if enabled)\nWin + H \u2014 Voice typing\nWin + Shift + S \u2014 Screenshot snip (tool)\nWin + D \u2014 Show/hide desktop\nWin + M \u2014 Minimize all windows\nWin + Ctrl + Space \u2014 Switch input language/keyboard\nWin + Space \u2014 Switch keyboard layout (when multiple layouts)\nWin + . (period) \u2014 Emoji panel / symbols\nWin + Z \u2014 Snap Layouts (layout menu)\nWin + Left/Right (with window focus) \u2014 Snap window to half\nWin + G \u2014 Xbox Game Bar (if enabled)\nCtrl + Shift + Esc \u2014 Task Manager (direct)\nAlt + Tab \u2014 Switch apps (hold Alt to preview)\nCtrl + Shift + Click (on app in taskbar) \u2014 Open new instance of app",
